&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Integrated Product Marketing Specialist&lt;/span&gt; is a hands-on, execution-focused role responsible for driving awareness, adoption, and commercial success of Phoenix Contact’s industrial networking, connectivity, and communications solutions across key application areas, including Transportation, Energy, and Public Safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role combines solution marketing with integrated marketing execution, with a strong emphasis on digital content creation, website and CMS (Drupal) management, and campaign deployment. The Specialist develops and executes solution-based messaging, creates digital and visual assets, and manages marketing initiatives that directly support business growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a proactive and self-directed contributor, this individual identifies gaps, builds new solutions and content, and drives initiatives forward—not just supporting existing programs. Working cross-functionally with Product Management, Sales, and Industry teams, the role ensures effective go-to-market execution and customer engagement across digital and traditional channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development of a solutions-first marketing approach for industrial networking and communications technologies (e.g., switches, cellular, wireless connectivity) across Transportation, Energy, and Public Safety.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and prioritize target applications and market segments within these ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate product capabilities into clear, application-focused value messaging and customer-centric content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop application-focused materials, including digital content, solution overviews, use cases, and case studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage website content, including product pages, solution pages, and landing pages, using CMS (Drupal); apply basic HTML/CSS as needed to ensure accuracy and optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support SEO and digital marketing initiatives through content optimization, campaign landing pages, performance tracking, and continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute digital marketing campaigns, including email campaigns, lead-nurturing workflows, and marketing automation using Salesforce Marketing Cloud Account Engagement (Pardot).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and produce digital and visual assets (e.g., graphics, presentations, videos, and campaign materials) using Adobe Creative Suite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support product positioning and the development of product launch and sales enablement materials, including product briefs, presentations, and brochures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive execution of solution launches, campaigns, and go-to-market initiatives aligned with commercial objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify gaps in marketing content, campaigns, or positioning and proactively develop solutions to address them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor campaign and digital performance metrics and recommend optimizations to improve engagement and outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with Product Management, Sales, Engineering, and Marketing teams to align messaging with application and market needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support planning and execution of trade shows and events, including booth coordination, event content, and integrated campaign support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple projects and timelines to ensure deliverables are completed on schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate initiative by independently driving work forward while incorporating input from stakeholders as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of responsibilities by following through on commitments and demonstrating accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&

&lt;p&gt;Together, we are creating a sustainable world based on our passion for technology and innovation - we are searching for people who share this purpose with us to join our &lt;strong&gt;International Fellowship Program&lt;/strong&gt; based at our headquarters in Blomberg, Germany.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you will join a 2-year master program in Information Technology&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;at TH OWL University of Applied Sciences and Arts starting October 2026. During and between semesters, you will have chance to work on real life projects with our research and development teams from the very beginning while being supported on a guided development journey. Upon completion of the program, you will return to the US in a role within our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you can expect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A fully funded 2 years full-time master study with a global industry leading company, including a scholarship, a sponsorship for the tuition fees and a paid working student contract throughout the master study.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work approx. 19 hours/week while in school and approx. 35 hours/week while on breaks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full benefit package available through our German subsidiary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 years working experience abroad in Germany for a global acting company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full time role at Phoenix Contact US after graduation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Praxis experience with selected business areas during and between semesters, together with a master thesis in cooperation with our company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support in helping you develop professionally, both hard and soft skills, through mentorship, workshops, on-the-job learning, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Variety of networking events to get to know your peers and colleagues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree or equivalent in Electrical Engineering, Information Technology, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Mechatronics, or another closely related field of study.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum GPA of 3.0 (transcripts required).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to obtain US Passport.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to live, learn and work in Germany for at least two years.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must meet Germany Student Visa eligibility requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keen interest in pursuing a career in Automation Development and passionate about offering solutions for business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You work collaboratively, enjoy working in an environment of friendliness and honesty.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are self-driven, adaptive to change, and think analytically.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are ready to being engaged in both student and working life in an intercultural context.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working experience in a relevant area is preferable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge in German language is recommended.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
