&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an entry level training position within the manufacturing departments of the Development and Manufacturing organization. This position is a machine operator role that is coupled with an apprenticeship program to develop skills needed to perform as a Mechatronics Technician. A Mechatronics Technician installs, maintains, and repairs automated systems by combining mechanical, electrical, and computer skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The apprentice will participate in a department rotation program learning about the key processes involved in manufacturing. Additionally, the apprentice will receive 8,000 hours of education and on-the-job training outlined in a highly structured program to obtain certification from the United States Department of Labor as a Mechatronics Technician.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Phoenix Contact will cover 100% of the tuition costs for the Apprentice to obtain an associate&#39;s degree in Mechatronics.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn the technical side of Phoenix Contact products for a better understanding of production methods and resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn how to operate various equipment and machinery in the manufacturing area, first as the line operator with the continuous transition into a Mechatronics Technician&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn how to monitor and analyze equipment performance and take actions to optimize machine performance for efficient production.&lt;/li&gt;
